In this presentation we will discuss the entropy function formalism. In this formalism a function -the entropy function- is defined on the horizon of a black hole. We therefore first review the concept of black holes and their horizons. The main goal of the thesis was to compare to proposals to define an entropy function on black hole solutions of five dimensional theories of gravity, coupled to scalar fields and vector fields.}